U.S. Stocks Extend Losses as Moody’s Downgrades Bank of America

-- B y   M i c h a e l   P .   R e g a n
-- 
2011-09-21T16:31:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-21/u-s-stocks-extend-losses-as-moody-s-downgrades-bank-of-america.html
U.S. stocks extended losses after
Moody’s Investors Serivce downgraded the debt of  Bank of America
Corp. (BAC)   Bank of America slumped 2.9 percent after the ratings
company reducedthe rating.  The  S&P 500  slid to its lows of the session after the
downgrade, dropping as much as 0.8 percent to 1,192.61. The  Dow
Jones Industrial Average  lost as much as 74.63 points, or 0.7
percent, to 11,447.86 as of 12:30 p.m. New York time.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael P. Regan at 
 mregan12@bloomberg.net  